âš™ï¸ How to Run the Program

Open your Java IDE (e.g., IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, or VS Code)

Create a new Java project and add the code in a file named Main.java

Compile and run the program

Players take turns entering row and column numbers (0, 1, or 2)

Example Input:

Player X, enter your move (row and column 0, 1, or 2):
0 1

ğŸ¯ Game Rules

The grid has 3 rows and 3 columns.

Players take turns placing their mark (X or O).

The first player to align three marks horizontally, vertically, or diagonally wins.

If all cells are filled and no one wins, the game ends in a draw.

